cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.THEORY, cs.DS, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a modification of the asynchronous pi calculus, which is a formalism used to reason about concurrent systems. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely as the paper proposes a new combinator calculus. 
- cs.THEORY (Theoretical Computer Science) is relevant as the paper discusses the operational semantics of the calculus. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with the manipulation of data structures (names). 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is also less likely but possible as the paper proposes a new approach to concurrency that could have practical applications in software engineering.
